\begin_layout Standard
Detecting and blocking malicious domain names is an important part of security
 incidence response.
 Use of algorithmically generated and dictionary based domain names pose
 a challenge for security experts and network administrators as these names
 resemble legitimate domain names.
 Current state of the art for this task is inadequate for handling this
 task.
 The proposed model in this paper makes use of encoder blocks from Transformer
 based deep learning architecture for detecting malicious domain names as
 well as predicting the domain generation algorithm family.
 The proposed method is simple and doesn't require any hand crafted feature
 to be fed into the model for training.
 We empirically found that proposed model provides F1 score of 0.99 for detection
 and more than 0.98 for classification of domain generation algorithm on
 real world dataset.
